quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,1,"Nun. By the pen and what the scribes write."{1},footnotes:1:1
  68,2,"By your Lord's Grace, you are not afflicted with madness,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  68,3,"and surely yours shall be a never-ending reward,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  68,4,"and you are certainly on the most exalted standard of moral excellence."{1},footnotes:1:1
  68,5,"So you will soon see, and they too will see,"
  68,6,"which of you is afflicted with madness."
  68,7,"Surely your Lord knows well those who have strayed from His Way just as He knows well those who are on the Right Way."
  68,8,"Do not, then, yield to those who reject the Truth, decrying it as false;"
  68,9,"they would wish you to be pliant so that they too may be pliant."{1},footnotes:1:1
  68,10,"And do not yield to any contemptible swearer,"{1},footnotes:1:1